stalwart-description =
    Stalwart is an all-in-one mail and collaboration server written in Rust.

    It handles SMTP (inbound and outbound), IMAP, JMAP, CalDAV, and CardDAV
    in a single binary — no separate processes, no complex configuration.
    The built-in web admin UI allows managing domains, users, and delivery rules.

    Stalwart integrates with Kanidm via OIDC for single sign-on — users authenticate
    with their FreeSynergy credentials.

stalwart-features =
    - SMTP (server-to-server + mail submission)
    - IMAP with full folder synchronisation
    - JMAP (modern mail API)
    - CalDAV and CardDAV (calendar and contacts)
    - Web admin UI
    - OIDC single sign-on via Kanidm
    - Written entirely in Rust
